inn1.comm: a bit of swing, from leg stump across towards off, Marsh stays behind the line and defends to the off side
starts the swing from wider outside leg and takes the pads to slip down the leg for four leg byes.
again, starts the swing from outside leg stump and Marsh gets some pad on it down the leg. Dhoni puts in the dive to half-stop it
back of a length outside off, no movement. Right hander reaches out and lets it go
on the money this time, lands on middle and leg and straightens towards Paine, who stays behind the line and defends down the pitch
again, a hint of shape away from leg and gets the leading edge as Paine looks to close the face and work to the leg side. It goes safely towards short cover, no harm done
short ball, angles down the leg without straightening and it is worked towards the leg side
good length and line this time, draws Marsh forward with a length delivery and he feels for it, uncertain of the movement. Safely played to the leg side
on a length and angling into the left hander, who works it off the front foot to short midwicket
this one shapes away from outside off, not much of pace off the track it gently bounds up from back of a length as Marsh shoulders arms
over-pitched on off stump, Marsh does not capitalise. Worked from outside off straight to mid on
and Nehra begins with a maiden. Back of a length on middle and leg, Marsh looks to work it square off the back foot but can't get it away.
good length ball, straightens from off stump as Paine plays from the crease to the off side
that's a pearler from Praveen. Lands on a length outside off and rears up as it darts away from Paine, who thought it was a rope and then found it was a snake and yanked his bat away
wider outside off, again nice shape outside off as Paine reaches out and lets it go
Lucky! Paine chips out to get to the pitch and negate the movement, but still can't get there. He gets an inside edge as he waves at it without conviction and it screams past the off stump for four.
stays in the crease this time and covers the line on off stump to defend to the off side
Should I play it? Should I leave it? Paine was undecided and the ball hit the bat as he was drawing it back outside off. It runs down to third man for a single
no movement for Nehra, banged short and angled across Paine, it does not deviate and the bounce is low too as Dhoni covers it
sprayed on the pads and Paine looks to nurdle it round the corner. Goes very fine, off the pads I reckon, and Dhoni cleans up
angled across again from back of a length, Paine reaches out and opens the face to dab it fine for a single
lets a short of length ball go outside off. On the second bounce to Dhoni. Hmm.

rattle! Marsh is gone. Nehra keeps it on that length outside off, and despite the lack of movement, there is enough doubt in Marsh's mind, thanks to the slowness, the uneven bounce and the steady lines, as he plays from the crease without conviction. Healthy inside edge crashes into the castle.
back of a length outside off, Clarke stays in the crease and defends to the off side
very slow pitch this, Paine stays back and runs the ball from outside off towards third man for one
this one is on the money and Clarke nearly plays all over it as he looks to work to the onside. Need to time the lunge perfectly on this pitch
this one is outside off and Clarke covers the line well to defend to the off side
another one on the money and Clarke is staying back - not a bad idea when the ball is not on the stumps - and defending to the off side
ooh, that's on a length outside off and Clarke gets into a mess as he looks to work it to the off side. Nearly sneaks in off inside egde, but he closes the gap
slower ball this time, Clarke looks to work it from middle and leg towards the on side, but can't quite time it
floated on a length at 120.5 kph and it angles across the right hander, who gets into the cover drive but can't time it at all
shorter outside off and more pace on it - 130 kph - Paine times it well as he cuts it straight to point. Guess who is back there - Yuvraj Singh.

almost another chop on to the stumps, that could be the theme of the day. Nehra keeps it back of driving length as Paine looks to cut it without much room to work with. It bounces near his feet and goes over the stumps.
more width on offer this time and he again looks to cut. Can't find the gap though
Right, he has had enough, so stays back, opens up the off side and looks to carve this over the off side. Thick outside edge down to third man where debutant Tiwary fields

walks out and in line with off stump to try and work it around his pads to the on side. Would have been in trouble if that had hit his pads, but he managed to work it off the legs to midwicket. Can't find the gap though.
back of a length on off stump again as Paine nervously tries to defend. Inside edge goes square on the leg side as Praveen oohs and aahs
back of a length again, on and around off stump. Clarke can't get forward and plays it out to the off side
this one is on middle and leg, Clarke tries to work it off the pads to the leg side. Straight to mid on
fuller on the pads as Clarke tries to flick. Straight to midwicket again. An opportunity missed this time.

another one on the pads and Clarke turns it around the corner to the right of Ashwin at square leg. He takes the single and gets off the mark as Ashwin's throw balloons in slowly to the non-striker's end
length ball on middle and off, no adventurism from Paine who stays in the crease and defends to the on side
angled across Clarke from over the wicket and he punches it with some conviction to mid off for a single
fullish on off and middle, angling across at 130 kph as Paine looks to open the face and run it to the off side.
lands this on middle and leg, works it off the pads to the leg side
back of a length again, Paine can't do anything with these lengths, so he just defends from the crease with the half-forward movement

this was a-coming. Paine has been pained into a suicidal dismissal here. He tried this before, and got away with it. He again chips out, can't reach the pitch, the ball does not come onto the bat and he closes the face early as he tries to flay over the on side. It bobbled up off the inside half straight to mid on. Gone.
full on middle and of, Hussey plays from the crease - would have been better playing off front foot - and squeezes it out to the off side
turned behind square for a single, Hussey back on strike.
hmm, Praveen gets it to straighten from off stump as Hussey comes half-forward looking to prod. Played off bat and pad down the pitch

there are three people on the off side inside the circle, but that's not a problem for Hussey who unfurls a delightful cut to thread a gap between those fielders into the cover boundary. Not short enough for the cut, and not quick enough to get the timing right, but that's not a problem for Hussey.
lets this one go outside off, from a length. Not much movement
on the stumps this time and Hussey covers the line and drives straight to mid off
slow off cutter, Hussey spots the change in pace and defends it easily to the off side
over-pitched on off stump and punched straight back by Clarke. Vinay does not make the effort to bend and stop in his follow through. Ashwin from mid on runs across to his right and does the honours
another delight from the Hussey box of shots on tough wickets. This was over-pitched and Hussey had the room, band Hussey got into position early to carress it through the covers for four
was that an off cutter? Hussey spots it and waits for it to come on from the leg stump line and defends to the off side

smooth. Vinay has started in wayward fashion and Hussey has cashed in. This one is on the pads, Hussey spots the length early and clips it neatly through the leg side for four. Kohli runs back from midwicket, and in Brad Hogg's words he was, "diving for the pool, but there is no water there".
fullish on middle and off, Hussey comes forward and plays to the off side of the pitch
Hussey closes the face a touch early as he tries to work it off the pads and gets a leading edge towards mid off. It stayed along the ground through out
Back of a length on off stump as Clarke covers the line and punches into the covers

that shot is a masterpiece in the art of timing. Not full enough to be driven and it does not quite come on to the bat from outside off. Clarke pushes forward and makes all the momentum with his bat speed, and makes contact on the up with the meat of the bat to find the gap between the bowler and mid off.
fuller this time and Clarke plays it more watchfully
full on the stumps and Clarke falls into the off drive, straight to Kohli who is standing on uncharted territory
works this into the covers where a fumble allows the single. Raina misfielded there, believe it or not.
very slow slower ball, wide outside off and Hussey wants nothing to do with it. Double bouncer to Dhoni.
Clarke motions out of the crease and looks to flick Vinay through midwicket. Yuvraj stops, does not collect, yet gets ready to throw.. and stares Hussey back into the crease. If looks could kill!
a hint of inward movement, Clarke tries to play around the pads to the leg side, but can't beat mid on
better from Vinay, he is hitting more Praveenesque lengths here. Clarke gets half forward, looking to cover any movement and defends to the off side
Clarke jumps out, but Vinay keeps it very short as Clarke hits it hard into the covers
and again, Clarke tries to make some pace happen by driving hard on the up. But he can't get enough momentum and punches it straight to mid off
fuller outside off and Clarke square drives on the rise towards point. Maiden from Vinay.
sprays the first ball of his spell into Hussey's pads. Meat and drink for Hussey who works it without fuss off the pads for four, to the left of midwicket inside the circle
keeps it very short outside off and Hussey stays back to open the face and run it square. Can't beat point though, who nearly concedes an overthrow with a needless shy at the stumps
another one on the pads, Hussey waits on this one and nurdles it fine for a single
cat and mouse stuff. Clarke darts out of the crease, Nehra possibly saw him coming and kept it very full and very wide outside off. Clarke plays it defensively to the covers
Clarke is out of the crease again, Nehra keeps this short on the pads and Clarke does not manage to make decent contact
another one on Hussey's pads - this over has been an aberration given the way Nehra started - and again worked towards square leg for one
back of a length and angling in, Hussey calmly drops it to the off side off the back foot and takes an easy single

Ashwin makes a mess of it at mid off. Drifts into Clarke's pads and he flicks it wide of mid off, as Ashwin runs across and tumbles. He moved very slowly there and the ball had already scooted past for four
full on middle and off, Clarke drives it crisply towards mid off
stifled appeal from Vinay who gets a bit of inward movement from outside off. Clarke pushes outside the line and gets a bit of bat and pad on it.
short ball, rises slowly as it angles into Clarke who stays in the crease and works it off the hips for one
full outside Hussey's off stump as he looks for the steer past point. Can't beat the fielder this time
on a length outside off, not much movement as Clarke defends
straighter this time and Clarke works it off the pads towards midwicket
full on off and Hussey reaches out to play it siftly into the covers for one
full on off and Clarke looks to drive, but gets too close to the ball and squeezes to the off side
this one is shorter and Clarke stays back to play it square on the off side for one
full on off and Hussey plays watchfully to the off side.
angles the first ball into Clarke's body as he walks out and gets inside the line to work it to the leg side for one
short ball outside off, Hussey looks to punch it off the back foot but can't beat Raina at cover
good length, keeps it outside off and not full enough for Hussey to drive. He looks to drop it to the off side, but can't get it away for one
misfield in the covers by Raina. Hussey drives on the up, and Raina should have stopped that as he tumbled to the right. Lets it go and it is a couple. The weather must be quite oppressive.
full on off and middle, Hussey punches it out to the off side
back of a length outside off and Hussey again stays back as he looks to punch on the rise. Mid off runs across to the left to stop it
tosses up on middle and off, Clarke hurries out and takes it from middle to work it behind square to the off side.
whoa, full on middle from round the wicket, Hussey is early on the reverser sweep and the ball breaks from middle and hits the back of his bat to go towards short third man for one
back of a length outside off, Clarke motions out and can't get it away
he's chipped out again and gets to the pitch, but can't get it past mid on
Clarke works this into the covers and picks a single
full on middle and off, Hussey plays it watchfully into the off side after reaching out
full and wide outside off, Clrake reaches out and drives into the covers for one
full on middle and off, Hussey works it towards mid on, but Yuvraj dives across to his left and saves the single. Well done.
on the pads and Hussey works it square, looking for two. Saurabh Tiwary hurries across from fine leg and keeps him down to one
Clarke skips out again, takes it on the full and works it towards wide long on for one
very full on Hussey's middle stump and he works it watchfully to long on for another single

huge appeal for lbw turned down. Full from Yuvraj, on middle and off as Clarke bounds out of the crease. Hits him on and around off stump as he misses the flick. Was he too far down? Was he outside the line? Leg bye taken towards third man. It landed on leg and was straightening. Might have hit middle and off, or might not have. Clarke was well forward.
turning in from middle and off, a bit of sharp turn there, but Clarke covers the spin and works it to the leg side
Hussey picks a single. They are turning the strike over well.
full on the stumps and worked straight between the bowler and mid on. Kohli at mid on does well to field it.
short this time, Clarke stays back and taps it into the covers for one
full on leg and turning away, Hussey leans out and plays it with the spin to the off side. Another single
short and enough room outside off for Clarke to lean back and run it square for one
speared in from well wide of the crease and short. Clarke plays it with the angle towards midwicket
full and wider outside off, Hussey is drawn into the drive but can't beat cover
straighter this time, full and on off stump, Hussey drives it down to long off for one

lovely play from Clarke here. He skips out, ensuring that he does not get too close to the ball, and hence has the room to free his arms and go over the covers. Inside-outed to perfection over the infield and well wide of long off running across.
full on off stump and Clarke works it off the pads to midwicket

that is as delicate as they come. Back of a length outside off and turning in. Clarke taps it so softly to the off side, you barely saw the bat make contact with the ball there. Single inside the circle
worked off the pads by Hussey - he will do this all day - and a single behind square on the leg side
whoa, Clrake advances down and Ashwin drops it short., looking to spin one across and down the leg. Clarke just about manages to keep it out to the leg side for one
Hussey rocks back and works this square on the leg side for one
the carom ball, dropped too short for impact, as Clarke pre-meditates the paddle lap-sweep. Gets it away behind square leg for one
tossed up generously outside off and Clarke drives straight to that fielder at neither here nor there mid off.
on the pads this time as Clarke skips out and works it off the pads wide of mid on
length ball outside off as Hussey leans out and drives straight to cover
shortens the length, Hussey waits for it to break back in and taps it square for one
short and turning away from Clarke who thrusts bat and pad out as he adjusts for the spin. Single towards point
full on off and Hussey drives firmly to wide long on for one more.
full and trickling down the leg, Hussey happily works it behind square for one more
back of a length and turning in sharply. Clarke stays back, spots the spin and works it to midwicket
full on off and driven nicely towards long off, Vinay bustles across to his right and tumbles to field that. Well done.
full on middle and turning across Hussey who again looks to work it softly with the spin. Can't find the gap

whoa, Hussey nearly holed out to a half-tracker. It was bad ball, spinning away from outside off as Hussey looked to pull. Hardly middled it, and it landed a few metres away from Praveen at cow corner

Clarke this time, ships out and tries to slam a ball that does not come on to the bat, down the ground. It goes no where. Lands somewhere between midwicket and wide long on, where there's no one to take the catch
Clarke advances again, and works it from off and outside towards wide long on for one
full on off and Hussey tries the tip and run routine. Can't beat cover this time
over-pitched outside off and Hussey drives out to wide long off for one
speared in from wide of the crease as Clarke looks to work it leg side. Can't quite get it away
that was quicker and flatter, took Clarke's pads as it hurried across without much spin. Leg byes down to fine leg as Dhoni appeals.
slower and more flight outside off, Clarke reaches out and drives through wide mid on
full on the pads and Hussey punches firmly off the toes to midwicket for one
worked with the spin through square leg for one
dropped shorter and flatter, quicker tgriygh the air. Raina is holding the ball back to see Hussey's movements. Hussey cuts without timing to the off side
again holds it back and hurries it into Hussey who plays for non-existent turn. Keeps it out though
drifts onto middle and leg this time and Hussey works it square for one
shorter to Clarke and it goes down the leg with the spin as he dinks it along for a coule to fine leg.
full toss on the pads and Hussey misses out as he times the flick well, but can't beat a quickly moving Kohli at deep midwicket. He collects and throws back in a trice.
shorter and straightening from off and middle into Clarke, who waits for the deviation and works against the spin for a single to square leg
Hussey blasts that one through the covers. Over-pitched outside off and Hussey was waiting for it. He got to the pitch and smote it through to the right of Vijay at cover. Lovely timing.
holds it back outside off and Hussey waits for it to come in and drives down the ground for one
speared on the pads and deviating into Clarke who has no problem working it to the leg side for another one.
short and turning away from Hussey, who can't beat cover with his cut
short and turning into Clarke who picks the length early and cuts behind square for one
full outside leg and Hussey drills it down to wide long on for one more
Pup chips out and looks to flick it with the spin, but can't beat midwicket
Raina holds it back this time as Clarke again skips out, but he adjusts to close the face and work it to the right of midwicket
Hussey drives on the up through the covers where Dhawan lets it go. Single to the deep
very short and asking to be shellacked. Clarke can't quite time it, though. On the bounce to deep midwicket
slow and tossed up on the pads, Clarke tries to flicks it past midwicket. Can't beat the fielder though
skips out again, does Clarke but can't get the straight drive past the bowler
aha, gamesmanship there. Yuvraj spears it down the leg, expecting Clarke to come down the track, but he does not. Wide called
fuller on leg and Clarke drives between mid on and midwicket for one to the deep
full toss on the pads and Hussey misses out. Flicked straight to Nehra who tumbles at short fine leg and makes a smart save
short and turning in, Hussey punches it back towards Yuvraj who half-stops but can't prevent the single
short and turning away from Hussey, who stays bacl and works it against the spin to midwicket for one

Clarke has played his best innings on the tour, and what a shot to bring up the fifty landmark. Slightly short and slightly wide outside off, and placement was of the essence as Clarke rocked back and fsent it purring through the covers with a cut shot.
quicker one, hurries through without much spin as Clarke looks to dab to third man
on the stumpos this time and Clarke works it with the spin to the leg side for one
Hussey picks a single into the covers. The engine rolls on, menacingly revving at third gear. India need to put the brakes on.
another single, short and turning in from outside off, cut into the covers for one more
speared in on the pads, Clarke stays back in the crease and nurdles to square leg for one
dainty stuff from Hussey, waits for it to turn into him from off stump and drops it to the off side. Single as easy as you like it.
faster and flatter on middle stump, Clarke stays back and plays with the angle to the leg side for one
over-pitched outside off and Hussey drives it out to wide long off to reach a fine half-century. He has been the prime mover of this innings.
full on the pads as Clarke looks to charge out. He works it straight to midwicket
full on off stump this time and Clarke drives with the spin to wide long off for one
on a length around off stump, not much movement, but comes into Clarke with the angle as he looks to work it around to the leg side. Can't quite get it away
fuller outside off, Clarke reaches out into the cover drive and they run across for a quick single to Dhawan in the covers
angled into Hussey's pads with the angle from round the wicket and Hussey flicks it square for a couple. Poor bowling, with the field set on the off side
on and around off stump this time and Hussey punches it to long off for one more

run-out chance, but Dhawan misses from mid off. That shaped in from outside off and Clarke pushed it towards mid off and took off for the single. Dhawan covered ground quickly, but missed with his throw. Would have been touch and go.
textbook defence from Hussey to an over-pitched offering on middle and leg
good length, on off stump. Clarke reaches out and looks to punch down the track, but can't beat the bowler
chips to the off side as the ball angles into him from off stump, and picks a couple behind deep square leg. This partnership has been a lesson on middle-overs batting in an ODI.
short and wide outside off, Clarke is out of the crease as he looks to guide it to the right of Yuvraj at point. Fumbled, but no run conceded

another misfield, what's happening here. Single conceded this time by Vijay at midwicket. Short ball angled into Clarke who flicked straight to Vijay, who deflected it to Dhawan, allowing them to steal one
very short and Hussey latches on with a pull over the in-field. He focused on control rather than power this time and kept it down to deep square leg as Tiwary ran across to field. Couple taken.
thumped! Over-pitched outside off and Hussey drills it on the up through wide long on as the fielder in the deep makes a vain attempt to tumble and save.
slants one into the pads, flicked towards midwicket, straight at the fielder
short of a length and nips into the batsman, who punches it back past the bowler, Clarke sets off for a single, Hussey too before they realise mid-on has stopped the ball and both scurry back
gets a couple this time, well run after pushing it to deep midwicket, where Ashwin is a bit slow getting to the ball
gets forward and pushes the ball towards Yuvraj at point

whoah, whats was Clarke thinking. he punched the ball back to the bowler, who extended his left hand to pluck the ball, Clarke was charging down the ground, Vinay shies at the stumps, a direct hit and Clarke was a goner, he misses though
dabs it to Yuvraj at point and sets off for a tight single, direct hit would have made things close
into the pads, defended to the leg side
full ball on middle and off, eased towards mid-off
whipped towards long-on for a comfortable single
'Two' Clarke shouts after tucking a shortish ball on the pads towards backward square leg
fullish ball this time, pushed towards mid-off
on middle and leg, flicked towards Dhawan at short midwicket
starts with a fullish ball, Hussey plays a reverse paddle-sweep to get it to third man
more conventional stroke this time, pushed towards mid-on
tossed up by Ashwin, Clarke comes down the track and drills the ball to the bowler's right, Ashwin moves to cut it off, gets a hand to it but can't stop the single
Hussey plays it late, dabbing it to short third and looking for the single but it goes straight at the fielder so Hussey decides against it
gets one this time, whipped wide of a diving Dhawan at midwicket
a wristy shot from Clarke sends the ball scurrying towards deep midwicket, to the left of the fielder, giving time to return for the second
Hussey moves forwards and works the ball to midwicket
Hussey reverse-sweeps again, not the fine paddle of the previous over, this is a powerful stroke towards backward point for four
short ball on the pads, swept behind square leg
defended back towards the bowler, who dives to his right to field
another dot ball, defended towards the left of the bowler
fullish ball pitching on middle, Clarke goes for the sweep and misses, hit on the pads, prompting a huge shout for lbw, umpire turns it down as it looked to be heading down leg
full on the leg side, easy single to midwicket
slices it to point, placement isn't great

this time the lbw appeal is upheld, Hussey looked to be tiring over the past few overs, a short of length ball, Hussey looks to pull that one, he misses and is struck on the thigh pad on the back leg in front of middle and leg, that was going on to hit, no doubt, the umpire didn't have any either
plays his first ball watchfully, blocked to the off side
again gets a big stride in as he defends to the off side
on middle and leg, White stays in the crease and pushes the ball to the leg side
Clarke's turn to shows us his forward-defensive technique
he charges out of the crease and plays an inside-out towards sweeper cover, White pushes Clarke to return for the second
tucked off the pads towards deep midwicket for a single
length ball outside off, White says 'No' after pushing it towards short cover, some sloppy fielding from Raina gives away the single
Clarke continues to collect the easy single, again on legstump, nudged behind square
way down the leg side, would have been a wide if White had let it go, instead he shovels it to deep backward square leg
quiet start to the over, defended back to the bowler
strays onto the pads, guided down towards fine leg
outside off, Clarke drops the ball towards short cover, White wants the single but Clarke sends him back
another single to Clarke, comes down the track and punches the ball towards long-on, risk free
pushed towards mid-on by White
some turn for Ashwin, White finds the man at square leg this time, another tidy over from Ashwin
starts with a back of length ball angling across the batsman, who steers the ball towards backward point
length ball this time, White gets forward and eases the ball towards mid-off
a touch shorter, the first attempted big hit from White, gets a bottom-edge towards midwicket
Shot! White gets his first boundary, a typically bludgeoned hit, a bit of width, White throws his bat at it, gets it past short cover and long-off had no chances
delicate this time, closer to offstump, White plays with soft hands towards point and scampers a single
slower ball from Nehra to end the over, Clarke does what he has done all innings, takes a safe single, all along the ground to long-off
on middle stump, Clarke backs away and plays the ball towards point
length ball on off, driven back towards the bowler
spins towards leg, Clarke whips it to midwicket for a single
sharp spin into offstump, White plays it late, stays in the crease and guides it behind point
Clarke continues to use his feet to the spinners, waltzing down and helping the ball to long-on
jabbed towards backward point, White wasn't sure there was a single, Clarke had no doubts, he charged through for the run and White followed suit
pushed back towards the bowler, Nehra can't make stop the ball completely, batsmen are confused whether to go for the single or not, decide against it finally after a bit of panic
White searches for the big hit, drags it towards the leg side for a single
good cricket that, Clarke had skipped away a long way from leg stump, Nehra followed him, Clarke adjusted, got inside the line of the ball and guided it to fine leg for a boundary
ooh, close call for Clarke, he flicked the ball towards midwicket, a bit of an edge takes it in the air towards the fielder but lands wide of him
fullish ball outside off, driven down to long-on for a n easy single

'Noooo,' screams Clarke after playing the ball towards short cover, Clarke had moved away from leg, Nehra cramped him for room and the batsman still managed to get it toward Raina, who dived and stopped the ball
slow, length ball outside off, White plays it uppishly towards mid-off for a single
length ball angling into leg, Clarke comes down the track and punches the ball towards extra cover, yet another fumble, both batsman made it nearly halfway down the pitch before turning back
slower ball from Vinay, short of length and outside off, Clarke comes down the track and plays it to the right of Vinay, who dives but can't get a hand on the ball
a good-looking stroke from White for a single, a fullish ball on middle and leg, White moved away from leg stump, driven along the ground to long-off
again a slower ball, 101.5kmh, length ball, Clarke gets forward and plays the ball towards long-on

a full toss to end the over, on middle and leg, again White had moved away from the stumps, again he punches it down to long-off for a single, good over for India that, Australia still searching for the next gear
on legstump, batsman moves towards off and tucks the ball towards short fine, Vinay makes a despairing dive to save his team three runs
on middle and leg, whipped towards the leg side for a single
a full toss outside off, an outside edge as White attempts his favourite lofted drive towards deep extra cover, ball bounces before reaching the keeper
White makes room and plays the ball towards short third man
shortish ball on middle stump, Clarke moves away from legstump, driven down the track

this time White makes contact as he attempts the lofted drive, not enough power to take it over the rope, Raina nearly pulls of a brilliant, diving catch at long-off, can't hang on, but does enough to prevent the ball from good for a boundary, Raina made plenty of ground and should actually have gone for it with both hands, he stuck out his right hand and the ball didn't stick
boundaries remain elusive for Australia, Clarke gets a single to the leg side
a yorker on the pads, whipped towards deep square leg
finally White gets the boundary he has been searching for, makes room and absolutely hammers it past long-off for four, the power on that stroke was awesome
length ball on middle, turned towards midwicket by White
Ashwin dives to his left at short fine to cut off Clarke's shot, it was a legstump delivery that Clarke seemed to have put away for four, Praveen is happy with that bit of fielding
fullish ball on the pads, guided to deep midwicket for a single
and he is invited by a humongous straight hit, a length ball in the slot, white says thank you and  that six brings up the 50 stand
drilled down to long-on for a single this time

Clarke joins in the fun, nearly takes the head of Billy Bowden as Clarke comes down the track and clubs the ball straight back, Bowden goes down quickly and he needed to, he would have had to retire hurt otherwise, Bowden takes a moment to compose himself
Clarke moves to 99, a lovely shot from Clarke, makes room again and cut the short of length ball towards sweeper cover, this is turning into a very expensive over
Clarke gets to his fifth ODI century, he's had a wretched Test series, great start to his ODI series though, turned the ball towards midwicket for the single that brings up the landmark
White brings out the lofted straight hit again, not enough power on it this time, gets to the fielder at long-on on the bounce
overpitched delivery, driven crisply along the ground, back past the bowler, Tiwary runs across from long-on to cut it off
Nehra keeps it full, eased along the ground towards long-off
short of length on the pads, tucked towards short fine leg
White comes down the track again, searching for the straight hit again, gets an inside edge that sneaks past the keeper for a boundary
another boundary behind the wicket for White, this time it was intentional, a fullish delivery, White backed away and opened the face to guide the ball past the short third man for four
last ball of the Powerplay is defended towards short cover for a single, 49 runs in the last five overs
rubbish delivery to start, full toss outside leg, White manages to place it to deep backward square leg, Praveen lucky that was guided for a boundary
full toss outside off this time, Clarke had moved away from leg, threw his bat at it, can't get it past point

typical White stroke to bring up his half-century, lovely flowing hit straight over the bowler's head and towards the sightscreen, injures a spectator as well, it bounces by the side of the sightscreen and bounced sharply onto the first tier, taking an elderly man by surprise, hit in the face, he's getting some medical assistance now
another full toss, steered wide of mid-on for a single
another massive six, again straight down the ground, the spectators better watch out, this time the ball lands in a lawn sort of area and doesn't bounce into the stands
another six, Australia turning it on here, this time it is Clarke, gets on knee and powerfully sweeps that one beyond deep midwicket, biggest six so far
pushed towards cover for a single
White again throws his bat, looking to clobber the ball, doesn't get hold of it and it flies towards deep backward point
White wants a six every ball now, makes room and looks to clear deep extra cover, again the ball lands short of the fielder
Australia making merry, India's perennial failing at the haunts them, a low full toss on the pads, White places that wides of long-off to pick up four more
dot ball to end Nehra's spell, White doesn't get bat on ball and Dhoni collects
a yorker just outside off, Clarke looks to get it away to point, hits the bottom of the bat and rolls to the off side
Wow, White gets a gift from his Royal Challengers Bangalore team-mate, a juicy full toss and White has the spectators scurrying by depositing that in the second tier beyond long-on
White wants to repeat that shot but gets a thick inside edge and that runs away past Dhoni to fine leg for four
Vinay gets away with a length ball well outside off, White had moved away from the stumps and doesn't offer a stroke
Brutality, another full toss and White hammers that one over midwicket, a flat, powerful hit for six more, Vinay Kumar can't wait for this to end

The perfect finish for Australia, six more, but a delicate six (if that's possible), a low full toss and White's timing to get that away beyond midwicket was sensational, totally different to the previous shot which was a brute force hit

inn2.comm: starts with a length ball outside off, left alone by Dhawan

Oh dear, that's the end of Dhawan, a debut duck for him, he's shattered and the crowd has gone silent, a back of a length ball that sneaks in between bat and pad to take offstump, not much footwork from Dhawan as he looked to keep that out
length ball on offstump, defended to the off side
opens the face and guides the ball towards backward point for a single
length ball outside off, Vijay is happy to leave that to the keeper
a lot fuller this time, Vijay defends towards the off side, McKay and Australia couldn't have asked for a better over to start
starts nicely with a short of length ball angling across the batsman, who shoulders arms
short and wide, Kohli mistimes a shot towards cover
full and outside off, sneaks under Kohli's bat, and moves in after the stumps to baffle Paine, who misses and gives away four byes
full ball outside off and left alone
too wide outside off, he'll have to re-bowl that, Starc has been bowling around 140 kmh this over
short of length ball on offstump, Kohli gets behind the line and defends solidly
swing and a miss to end the over, Kohli gets forward to try drive the ball towards extra cover, he is beaten by the angle of the delivery
McKay starts his second over with a delivery that seams in after pitching well outside off
length ball on offstump, Vijay plays a compact forward defensive
length ball on middle, inside-edged onto the pads as Vijay looks to flick it
a nice shot from Vijay for no runs, width on offer for him and he cracks that towards covers but can't beat the fielder
this time he does, overpitched just outside off, Vijay gets forward and drives it crisply past cover for four
short of length ball on middle and off to end the over, Vijay taps it back to the bowler, who throws it gently towards the stumps, hits the batsman on the pads and ricochets onto the stumps
well outside off, Kohli looks to carve it through the off, gets a bottom edge back towards the bowler
back of length and outside off, Kohli gets forward and drives past cover, off the toe end of the bat, so there wasn't enough pace on it to go to the boundary
good delivery from Starc, on offstump, Kohli defends towards the off side
short ball from Starc, Kohli gets another boundary by pulling that one, he didn't time it too well but had enough to clear the infield and roll away for four, it was a 141kmh delivery
full and on the pads, blocked to the legside
full and very wide, Kohli throws his bat at it, gets an edge towards third man for a single, a few yards either side and that would have been a boundary
back of length ball on offstump, tapped towards the leg side, zips through for a single
keeps it tight around offstump, Vijay guides the ball towards point
on middle and off, Vijay plays it towards midwicket and sets off for a single, a direct hit would have been very tight, Hopes can't get the direct hit though
two short covers in place but Kohli manages to bisect them, not timed though, gets a couple for his efforts
shortish ball on middle, defended back down the pitch
width on offer, nicely played down to third man, who has to sprint to his right to field that one, batsmen pick up two
134kmh ball outside off, guided to third man
short of length just outside off, punched to covers off the front foot
gets forward and taps it to short cover
overpitched and just outside off, driven to mid-off
Kohli wafts at it outside off, there is a massive appeal for caught behind from the fielders but nothing from the keeper or the bowler
full outside off, mistimes a drive towards cover
full ball outside off, Vijay gets forward and lofts it over both the short covers to pick up a boundary
well outside off, Vijay moves across and defends towards point
brilliant shot from Vijay, stands tall and cracks it through extra cover for four, driven on the up by Vijay, the crowd enjoyed that
on the pads, easy picking s for Vijay, tucked behind square leg
on middle and leg this time, Kohli leans across and works it to deep square leg
on middle stump, full delivery, defended back down the track
length ball just outside off, defended to the off side
shortish ball on off, defended off the back foot towards cover
length ball on off, gets forward and taps it towards cover
Hastings keeps it steady, around off, back of a length, blocked towards the off side
seams in a touch after pitching around off, Kohli taps it towards midwicket
shortish ball and very wide, Kohli flashes at it but can't beat point, so Hastings completes a maiden
short of length ball on offstump, defended towards point
slips down the leg side, that's a free run

McKay strikes again, he got Dhawan with a terrific delivery, this was an okay one, nothing alarming in it, just outside off, Vijay wanted to guide that one towards third man, gets a edge to the keeper
Yuvraj watchfully defends his first delivery, a length ball on the stumps, gets forward and blocks it
fuller this time, driven towards cover
short of length ball, angling across the batsman who leaves it to the keeper
a superb delivery to end the over, cuts the batsman in half, nips in after pitching short of a length on off, Yuvraj is clueless about it, and it sails over the stumps
full ball on middle and leg, whipped to deep square leg by Kohli
keeps Yuvraj quiet with his steady line, on offstump, defended cautiously
middle and off line, defended back to Hastings
tests Yuvraj with a bouncer, 135kmh, Yuvraj leans out of the way, it was outside off so Yuvraj wasn't troubled by it
the slower delivery from Hastings, 116kmh, tucked to short midwicket
Yuvraj gets his first boundary, a lovely whip sends it over the midwicket boundary after a few bounces, it was a full ball from Hastings on the pads, Yuvraj lifts his back leg as he dismisses that
length ball on offstump, defended to the off side
length ball just outside off, tucked towards mid-on for a single
length ball on the offstump, driven towards extra cover
shortish ball on middle stump, Kohli gets a single to the off side
short of length ball outside off, Yuvraj opens the face a touch to steer the ball past the keeper and fine of third man for four
length ball, driven firmly on the up, stopped by a diving short cover
short of a good length on middle, whipped away behind square for a single
lands on a good length on middle, defended solidly towards mid-on
short of a good length on the off, pushed off the back foot back to the bowler
pushes it full on middle, tries to push through straight but ends up opening the face just a little right at the end, into the off side for a single
banged in short outside off, shapes up for a pull, mistimes it to midwicket
a bit of width this time, reaches out and cracks it to point, straight to the fielder
on middle and off, just short of a good length, presents the full face while playing it back
full on middle, gets across and drives it sweetly but straight to mid-on
nipped back in a hint from a good length outside off, guided down to third man for a single
pitched up and driven but mistimed again, just wide of mid-off
fullish on middle, driven hard but straight to mid-on
stands tall and punches it straight to extra cover, steady progress
slides down the leg side and is called a wide
fullish on the off and is driven hard, straight to mid-off

punched off the back foot towards mid-on, Kohli calls for the single and Warner, substituting for McKay at mid-on, collects and aims but it's just wide, Kohli would have been short had that hit, missed run-out
on towards third man for a single
strays on the pads and he clips it fine, no one at fine leg and picks up a boundary
found the gap, was pitched full, he leant forward and sliced it between point and cover, it's a pacy outfield and it raced away
Yuvraj smacked that hard, off the meat but found extra cover
beautifully done, pitched up on middle, was in the slot and Yuvraj picked it to launch it over the bowler's head for four more, gaining in momentum is the Indian innings now
plenty of width and Yuvraj chases it but finds cover again
slower one bowled short but down the leg side, called a wide
gets forward and pushes it towards mid-off
full outside off, caresses it but again, does not pierce the field, straight to cover point
slightly short outside off, trying to nip it back in, guided down to third man for a single
fullish outside off, driven elegantly down the ground towards long-off for a single
bowls it on a good length on middle, pushed down towards long-on this time
short of a good length outside off, run down to third man for one more
pinching the singles now, fourth one in a row, played towards long-off
slower one bowled full on the off, drilled down the ground, Warner cuts it off running across from long-off
six in a row, clipped off his pads to fine leg to keep the strike
tosses it up, good flight, flicked slightly uppishly towards midwicket
reaches forward and works it around towards square leg, flighted again
round the wicket to Yuvraj, pushed off the front foot towards midwicket, they pick another run thanks to an overthrow, Hussey threw and Hauritz didn't pick it
pushed off the front foot back to the bowler
swept hard and gets four, fetched it from outside off and bisected that gap between deep square leg and deep midwicket
starts with a short one that's duly dispatched, short outside off, moves back and thwacks it hard to beat that gap between long-off and deep extra cover
pushed down the ground to long-off to raise the 50-stand
full toss outside off, driven hard, wide of deep extra cover for a couple of runs
pitched up on the off stump, wristily played back past the bowler for a single
reaches forward and plays it back to Smith
driven soundly past the bowler to long-off to keep the strike
pushed off the back foot to long-on, one more
really slow through the air, Yuvraj closed the face a touch too early while trying to play it into the leg side, it turned away to catch him on the back pad but was missing off
turned away wide of square leg for a single
turning in from a good length outside off, dabs it towards point for a single
comes down the track and drives it down to long-off, didn't quite get to the pitch there but played it well in the end
worked away towards midwicket
full toss, smacked down the ground to long-off for a single
another full toss, punched towards long-on for one more
quicker, short outside off, turning in, pushed uppishly towards extra cover
gets across and turns it around behind square for a single
flighted on the off, swats it hard down the ground, between long-off and long-on, a dual effort in the deep to keep it to two
closes the face there and turns it behind square for a single
short and turning in, taps it towards extra cover
flighted outside off, swipes it towards wide long-on for a single
quicker delivery, turning away, was trying to open the face there, it beat the outside edge
angling in to Yuvraj from round the wicket, pushed back to the bowler
driven down the ground to long-on for a single
turning in from a good length outside off, knocks it down in front of point for a single
shortish outside off, punches it off the back foot to extra cover
shortish, dabs it towards point from the crease
three dot balls, driven well but straight back to the bowler
just punches it past the bowler down to long-on for a single
slices it slightly though the intention was to hit straight, rolls towards point
fullish on the pads, flicks it through square leg, Shaun Marsh runs across and returns a good throw but they've completed the second comfortably
short, slapped towards long-on for a single
tossed up on middle from round the wicket, swept towards deep square leg for a single
flighted on middle, lovely on-drive to the right of long-on, just the single
half-century for Kohli, tossed up, drives it down to long-on after stepping out, steadied the ship after the early loss of India's openers

tries to work it to square leg, a fullish ball, is rapped on the pads but struck outside leg, well actually not, marginal call there, hawkeye shows it could have pitched in line and then spun towards middle and off but it was a borderline case there, can't be completely sure
shortish on middle, punched it off the back foot towards long-on for a single
taps it into the off side between point and cover
well fielded at short fine leg, whipped from the crease but Starc does well diving to his wrong side to prevent any runs
driven towards long-on for a single
played it towards long-off for one more
slowed it down slightly, tried to force it through the off side but was into the shot too early, missed
bowls it on a good length outside off, turning away, driven straight to extra cover
swept towards deep square leg for a single
pushed down the ground towards long-on for one more
saw him come down and pushed it quick on middle and off, Yuvraj came down the track and offered his pads
closer to the bat, gets forward and defends

appeal for run-out, driven hard down the pitch, Hauritz tries to field it, clips his fingers and crashes into the stumps at the non-striker's end, Kohli had not backed up too far and made it back just in time
bowls it on a good length outside off, pushed straight to extra cover
pitched it up on middle, got across and smote it but straight towards the fielder at deep square leg
edged and four, short of a good length, swung hard across the line, flew off the outside edge just wide of the diving Paine to the third-man boundary, breaks an eight-over boundary drought
pushed off the front foot towards the bowler
short on middle, knocks it down in front of midwicket
shortish outside off, tries to force it off the back foot past extra cover, gets a thick inside edge past square leg for a couple of runs
thought he would charge down and fired it down leg, Kohli didn't move an inch, wide called
nicely done, waited for it to turn in, got back and pulled it hard with the spin past the diving midwicket for a boundary
got across and tried to work it into the leg side, goes off the pad, they steal a leg-bye
knocks it down into the leg side for one more
works it behind square for one more
gets on the back foot and pinches a single past extra cover
turning in from a good length outside off, works it towards short fine leg who prevents the single
bowls it on a good length on the off, defended back to the bowler, he's on 49 now
shortish on the off, punches it down the ground towards long-off for a single to complete his half-century, these two have set up an interesting chase here
they're finding the boundaries more frequently now, short and wide and he slashes it hard past point, raises the 100-stand
short of a good length on middle, whipped past square leg for a couple of runs
excellent over for India this, pitched up and he times it beautifully, crunching it on the up wide of long-off and extra cover for four more
and finishes off by picking a single down to long-off to retain the strike
targeting middle and leg, worked away past square leg for a single
shortish outside off, slaps it wide of long-off for a single
pushed in the direction of long-on for one more
flighted outside off, chops it down behind point for a single
quicker through the air, drops it into the off side, thinks of a single, is sent back
quicker ball dropped short, pulled away towards deep backward square leg for a single
and is smashed for a boundary first up, a short ball on the off and is pulled handsomely over midwicket, off the front foot, four more
lands on a good length outside off, cracked towards deep cover for one more
slower one, the offcutter, bowled down leg and doesn't cut back in enough, wide called

Paine concedes four byes, that one kept really low, Yuvraj could not get his bat down in time and Paine, trying to collect it to his right could not get his gloves around it, Australia need a breakthrough badly
pushed into the off side on the front foot, towards extra cover
short, pitches outside leg and nips back in, struck high on the pads as he tries to work it across
slower one bowled full, driven down the ground for a single to long-on
short of a good length on middle and leg, gets back and punches it to mid-on
bangs it short on the leg stump, Yuvraj tries to turn the face but ends up getting a leading edge that falls safe
Kohli is cramping now, full toss outside off, pushed towards deep cover, in a bit of pain as he runs across the pitch
beaten all ends up, a bit of extra bounce and nipped away to escape the outside edge
bowls it on a good length outside off, chipped uppishly towards mid-off, falls well short
short delivery down the leg side this time, tries to glance it fine, a wide called
wide again, full outside leg stump this time, Paine dives to his right and collects
back on target, gets forward and dabs it towards cover for a quick single
Yuvraj looks to pull a shortish delivery, he misses and is hit on the thigh pad
on the pads, easily runs for Yuvraj, tucked towards deep midwicket
driven towards the mid-off for a single
length ball on middle and leg, defended back down the pitch
overpitched just outside off, driven along the ground to long-off for a comfortable single
well outside off, Kohli advances down the track and drives it towards extra cover
on the leg side, whipped off the thigh pad towards fine leg, Hasting races across and dives to his right to cut it off
Kohli's on the ground with another attack of cramps, he's clutching his face in pain, it was a full toss outside off, Kohli carved it to sweeper cover and immediately went down
back of length ball on offstump, defended towards point
a touch shorter from Starc, Yuvraj gets beaten outside edge as he looks to defend, nice tight line from Starc
back of length angling into legstump,Yuvraj gets a leading edge to the left of the bowler
ends the over with a quick yorker, Yuvraj manages to dig it out to the off side
starts with a back of length ball on middle and off, defended off the front foot to the leg side
outside off, poked towards cover
length ball, Yuvraj pushes it towards mid-off and wants the single, sent back by Dhawan

the famous McKay slower ball does the job, back of the hand delivery, touch short, Yuvraj went to pull it, he misses and the ball crashes into the top of off stump, massive wicket this, especially with Kohli struggling with cramps
length ball outside off, Raina leans across and pushes the ball towards cover
just outside off, steered towards backward point
length ball outside off, Kohli slaps it down to long-off
on middle and off, Raina gets off the mark by shuffling across the stumps and tucking the ball to square leg
overpitched ball heading into offstump, driven towards extra cover
short from Starc, Kohli flatbats it towards mid-on, there's confusion in the running, Raina and Dhawan finally take the run, Kohli grimaces in pain after playing that shot
well outside off, superbly timed steer from Raina send the ball flying to third man, good fielding down there

wonderful stroke to end the over, Kohli moves on to 88, slightly overpitched outside off, a lofted drive wide of long-off, lovely timing, it was a one-handed shot as well, the bottom hand came off as he played it
shortish ball, Raina nearly chipped it to short cover, he came charging down the track and chopped that one though it was short
full and outside off, dabbed through cover by Raina
width on offer, Raina gets his front leg out of the way and carves that over cover, brilliantly timed, little effort as he played that but it raced to the boundary
not that good a shot this time, comes down the track and drives it towards long-off, not off the middle of the bat
full ball on middle, whipped towards midwicket by Kohli for another single
back of length ball on middle and off, Raina eases it towards long-off and takes a single
length ball outside off, Raina pokes it towards cover
tossed up by Hauritz, fullish ball, driven to deep extra cover by Raina
full ball, Kohli blasts it back but Hauritz fields it
driven down the ground for another comfortable single
length ball turning into the pads, a wristy shot from Kohli sends the ball towards deep midwicket
a yorker from Hauritz, Raina squeezes it out towards cover, could have been very close if there was a direct hit
on the pads, tucked behind square leg for a single
superb placement from Raina, he was walking forward but the ball was a touch short, so he stayed back and glanced it wide of short fine leg for a boundary
mid-on came in after that previous four, fine leg went to the rope, Raina notes the change and smashes the slower ball from Hopes over mid-on for a boundary
Raina on the rampage here, a length ball is clobbered to wide long-on for a one-bounce four, India taking control here
length ball outside off, Raina places this one wide of sweeper cover and picks up a couple, this is turning into a very expensive over
driven to cover for a single with which Raina retains strike, he moves to 28 off 19
short ball sliding down leg, Raina misses out, swung down to fine leg by Raina
all to easy against Hauritz, length ball on offstump guided to long-on for a single
overpitched and angling into pads, Raina comes down the track and plays it uppishly towards long-off
length ball pitching on middle and off, another single to long-on
bowled from wide of the crease, Raina stays back and tries to guide it past backward point but can't beat the fielder
Raina keeps looking to come down the track, Hauritz sees him and fires it into the pads, Raina can only tap it back to the bowler
a wristy stroke from Kohli sends the ball towards deep midwicket, he moves onto 94
just outside off, enough width for Raina to open the face and steer the ball to third man for a single
width on offer, carved towards sweeper cover by Kohli
short of length ball heading for middle stump, poked towards cover
brilliant form Raina, stands tall and punches that low full toss past a diving mid-off, good timing on that stroke
Raina is in a hurry to get this over with, on the pads, Raina again places it perfectly, wide of the man at fine leg to get another boundary
comes forward and defends against Smith
well outside off, a touch short, Kohli looks to cut that but doesn't connect, Paine takes off the bails but Kohli is in the crease, no third umpire needed
this time Kohli moves towards leg and drives it towards wide long-on
moves to 98 by pushing the ball to wide mid-on
full toss well outside off, Raina comes forward and accepts the gifts, dispatches the ball past wide long-off for four
comes down the track and pushes the ball towards mid-off for a single
short of length ball on legstump, shovelled towards deep square leg by Raina

Kohli gets to his century, he celebrates enthusiastically, pumping fists and screaming, gets a standing ovation from his team-mates, he reached the milestone by moving beyond leg and steered the ball towards sweeper cover
slow bouncer down the leg side, Kohli goes for a flamboyant pull, he misses and it is called a wide
a yorker just outside off, driven towards wide mid-on
length ball angling into offstump, Kohli drives it down the ground towards long-off, bottom hand again comes off as he drives
Raina makes room and drives in the air towards long-off, easy run
Kohli looks to crack that one through the covers, but gets an inside edge towards midwicket. Sid Talya will take you through to the end
starts with conceding a four, full outside off, reaches for it and slices it over the covers for a boundary, the field has been brought in on the off side and it's duly punished
fullish on middle and leg, poor ball with a fine leg up and Kohli flicks it away fine for four more, this is highest score now
he wants to finish things off quickly now, slower one bowled on a length and he smashes it high and handsome into the stands over long-on

dropped. Hauritz spills it at point, width provided this time, Kohli slices it over point where Hauritz leaps and gets a hand to it but can't quite hold on, a tough chance but Australia need them to stick
short and drifted down the leg side but wasn't called a wide, the umpire reckons the batsman got a touch to it, off the shirt or something
pushed back down the pitch, gets a hand to it and it rockets into the stumps but Raina's back in, 16 off the over, India on top
six in the circle, shortish on leg stump, flicked into the on side for a single
Kohli has holed out with the task unaccomplished but he has certainly set the game up for India, full on middle and he smacks it cleanly but straight into the hands of Hopes at long-on
ooh, that didn't miss the stumps by much, was the offcutter, fell short outside leg, Raina came down to swipe it through square leg, missed and it missed the leg stump by an inch
closes the face and turns it towards square leg
slower one bowled full on middle and leg, driven down the ground to long-on for a single

Hastings takes two in this over, sends the off stump out of the round, kept a little low and nipped back in from a touch outside off, didn't bring his bat down in time as he attempted a cut and out went the off stump
slower one bowled full on middle, pushed down the ground to long-off for a single
pitched up on middle and off, pushed back towards the bowler
nipped back in from a good length outside off, guides it down towards third man for a single to get off the mark

slower one bowled full outside off, pushed towards extra cover who's at the edge of the circle, backs himself to complete that single and makes it in time with a dive to reach his half-century, a wonderful cameo this
angling in from round the wicket, fullish on middle, pushed past the bowler to long-on
fullish on the off, makes room and dispatches it over cover for a boundary, the field is in and he picked his spot, an inside-out shot, worth the risk
kept low again, short of a good length outside off, Tiwary was playing from the crease and missed it as it zipped under his bat
pitched it up on the off, driven straight to long-off
came forward and pushed it towards cover
drops it into the off side just wide of point for a single
pulled ferociously, dropped it short on middle, made some room and hammered it over midwicket
slower one bowled short on leg stump, flicked into the leg side behind square for a single
this is ending quickly, Hauritz tosses that up and it lands full on leg stump, Raina steps out while simultaneously making some room and launches it over long-on
bowled flat from round the wicket, pushed into the off side for a single

knocks it down into the leg side wide of square leg, the fielder from the deep takes a while to run in and Raina calls for a second to which Tiwary responds, had it been a direct hit at the non-striker's end, Tiwary was a gonner
pushed away wide of square leg for a single
Tiwary tickles it into the leg side for one more
pushes it wide of mid-on for one more
full on middle and leg, driven wide of midwicket for a single
fullish on the off, driven just wide of extra cover, can't find the gap however
that was a wild swat, slower one bowled short outside off, tries to whack it over midwicket, gets an inside edge onto this pads
bowls it on a good length outside off, pushed towards mid-on
bowls it short on middle, mistimes a pull towards mid-on
yorker on middle, dug out onto the pitch
short on leg stump, clipped off his pads down to fine leg for a single
bowls it on a good length on leg stump, pushed towards square leg, another dot ball to Tiwary
fullish, pushed back to the bowler
short and that will relieve a bit of pressure on the young man, short and it's pulled away over midwicket
India have won it comfortably in the end, pitched up outside off and it's eased into that gap between extra cover and mid-off for a boundary to seal a five-wicket win
